      <section eId="sec_51_6_3">
        <num>51-6-3</num>
        <content>
          <p>No action shall be sustained for deceit in a representation to obtain credit for another unless the misrepresentation is in writing and is signed by the party to be charged therewith.</p>
          <p>(Orig. Code 1863, § 2902; Code 1868, § 2908; Code 1873, § 2959; Code 1882, § 2959; Civil Code 1895, § 3815; Civil Code 1910, § 4411; Code 1933, § 105-303; Ga. L. 1992, p. 6, § 51.)</p>
